title: Fryns Syndrome: Epidemiological Overview
short_description: A clinical document describing Fryns syndrome as a rare genetic disorder with equal gender distribution and limited prevalence data.
long_description: This document provides epidemiological information about Fryns syndrome, a rare genetic disorder that affects both males and females equally. The content references a 1989 French study that reported an incidence rate of 7 cases per 100,000 live births, while noting the absence of more recent prevalence estimates in the literature. The document appears to be part of a clinical or research reference material addressing the rarity and demographic characteristics of this genetic condition.
